  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00038_187509_1523269774430&sectionId=44323&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00038_187509_1523269774430
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Limitation Act, 1963.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-`
  line `10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. 1st January, 1964,`
  line `vide notification No. S.O. 3118, dated 29th October, 1963, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
  line
  line `Amended in West Bengal by W.B. Act 18 of 1977.`
  line
  line `1st September, 1984,`
  line `vide notification No. S.O. 647(C), in respect of the State of Sikkim dated 24th August, 1984, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (44324)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "His Majesty's subject in India".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00038_187509_1523269774430&sectionId=44324&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00038_187509_1523269774430
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Nothing herein contained shall affect:`
  line
  line `(a) the capacity of any persons to act in the following matters (namely), marriage, dower,`
  line `divorce and adoption;`
  line
  line `(b) the religion or religious rites and usages of any class of ^1`
  line `[citizens of India]; or`
  line
  line `(c) the capacity of any person who before this Act comes into force has attained majority under`
  line `the law applicable to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (44325)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Age of majority of persons domiciled in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1999, s. 4, for sections 3 and 4 (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00038_187509_1523269774430&sectionId=44325&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00038_187509_1523269774430
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Age of majority of persons domiciled in India.(1) Every person domiciled in India shall`
  line `attain the age of majority on his completing the age of eighteen years and not before.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the age of any person, the day on which he was born is to be included as a whole`
  line `day and he shall be deemed to have attained majority at the beginning of the eighteenth anniversary of`
  line `that day.]`
